Part I - (Dataset Exploration Ford GoBike System Data)¶

by (Rania MEKRAZI)¶

Introduction¶

Introduce the dataset In this project, we will concentrate on visualizing the Ford GoBike System data set that includes information about individual rides made in a bike-sharing system covering the greater San Francisco Bay area.

Features included the dataset are:

  • Trip Duration (seconds)
  • Start Time and Date
  • End Time and Date
  • Start Station ID
  • Start Station Name
  • Start Station Latitude
  • Start Station Longitude
  • End Station ID
  • End Station Name
  • End Station Latitude
  • End Station Longitude
  • Bike ID
  • User Type (Subscriber or Customer – “Subscriber” = Member or “Customer” = Casual)
  • Member Year of Birth
  • Member Gender

Conclusions¶

Most of the bike riders, who participated in this trip were aged between 18 and 50 year

The number of males who participated in the Ford GoBike trips were more than females.

Most of the participants in the Ford GoBike trips were subscribers and not customers.

There is a moderate linear relationship between age and trip duration after log transformation of the two variables.

Subscribers took lesser time to complete the trip than customers.

Male participants appear to complete the trip faster than females.

Participants took more time to complete the trip on saturdays than other days of the week.

There were more males than females both in the customer and subscriber category.

Those who shared bike took slightly lesser time than those who did not share the bikes.

Regardless of the user type, male participants took lesser time to complete the trip than females.
